Avionics system for a sounding rocket:

Description: To calculate the height and GPS coordinates of a sounding rocket in real-time and transfer the data to the base station using wireless communication. The system was also designed to eject two parachutes one at apogee and another 1000 ft above ground. 

Hardware Used: Arduino nano, XBee Pro S3B, Adafruit BME280 pressure temperature and humidity sensor, black powder, E-match, Adafruit Ultimate GPS v3.

Software Used: Arduino IDE (C++), XCTU
